2729219.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1422729219/image_1422729219.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1422729219/image_1422729219.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1422729219/image_1422729219.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Anchiy/E+ via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Many market observers were likely holding their breath in advance of today\u2019s CPI release. The Federal Open Market Committee (\u201cFOMC\u201d) is set to hold their final meeting of the calendar year next week, and the November CPI report was expected to be the last</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1422729219/image_1422729219.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743615-november-cpi-second-consecutive-inflation-increase-not-cause-for-concern", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 19:42:05"}, {"id": "4743614", "title": "Safe Haven Demand Will Keep Gold Strong In 2025", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Gold investment concept. Illustration of growing bar chart.\" data-id=\"518118640\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1075px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">vchal/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>A number of analysts have styled 2024 as the \u201cGolden Year\u201d due to the yellow metal\u2019s outstanding performance over the past 12 months. It\u2019s not common for the precious metal to enjoy two consecutive years of conspicuous strength, but</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/518118640/image_518118640.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743614-safe-haven-demand-will-keep-gold-strong-in-2025", "pub_date": "2024-12-11 19:38:39"}, {"id": "4743609", "title": "Cash COWs And Buried Treasures: 2024 Performance Review", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1419459193/image_1419459193.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Until the cows come home\" data-id=\"1419459193\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1234px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1419459193/image_1419459193.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.